                            <comment id="21658" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 6 Jan 2007 10:07:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added support for this through the newly introduced &apos;early singleton access&apos; concept in AbstractBeanFactory, which ListFactoryBean, SetFactoryBean and MapFactoryBean inherit from. This exposes a JDK proxy for the respect interface now in case of a circular reference, instead of throwing a FactoryBeanNotInitializedException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The root of the problem here is that those FactoryBeans (and the tags in the &quot;util&quot; namespace that build on them) support a configurable collection class. They can&apos;t actually create the target instance until they have been fully configured, in contrast to a simple &amp;lt;list&amp;gt; / &amp;lt;set&amp;gt; / &amp;lt;map&amp;gt; tag with fixed default target class. The &apos;early singleton&apos; proxies address this now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
